            <section class="page-section" id="Definition">
<div class="gym">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="text-center">
            <h2 class="section-heading text-uppercase"> Definition </h2>


                <p> ISRO</p> <h3  class="section-subheading text-muted">The Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO) is the space agency of the Government of India. It is responsible for developing space technology and conducting space research for the benefit of the country.</h3>

                <p>NASA</p>  <h3  class="section-subheading text-muted">The National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) is the space agency of the United States government. It is responsible for conducting research and development in aeronautics, space science, and space exploration.</h3>

                <p>C++</p> <h3 class="section-subheading text-muted">C++ is a programming language that is widely used for developing software applications, including those used in scientific and engineering fields. It is known for its efficiency, speed, and versatility.</h3>

                <p>Electro-optic (EO/IR) systems</p> <h3  class="section-subheading text-muted">EO/IR systems are electronic systems that use optical and infrared sensors to detect, track, and analyze objects. They are commonly used in military and aerospace applications for surveillance, targeting, and reconnaissance.</h3>

                <p>Weather radar</p><h3 class="section-subheading text-muted"> Weather radar is a type of radar that is used to detect and track weather patterns, such as rain, snow, and hail. It is used by meteorologists to predict and monitor weather conditions.</h3>

                <p>Performance </p><h3 class="section-subheading text-muted">Performance refers to how well a system or process is functioning in terms of speed, accuracy, efficiency, and reliability. In the context of aviation and aerospace, performance can refer to the performance of aircraft, engines, and other systems. It is an important factor in ensuring safe and efficient operations.</h3>
               </div>
               </div>
               </div>

            </section>

