                                    <h2 class="text-uppercase">Aviation</h2>
                                    <p class="item-intro text-muted">Software</p>
                                    <img class="img-fluid d-block mx-auto" src="assets/img/portfolio/future-of-planes.jpg" alt="..." />
                                    <p>There are many software programs used when flying/making an aircraft. One of them is GE Digital. This software ensures customers safety and efficiency reach their destination. This software accomplishes this by “reducing operational disruptions, improving passenger experience, and making better decisions regarding real-time fleet health.”

                                        Other softwares are CATIA, Inventor, and Autodesk are three of the most common CAD software. These software are used to make mathematical suggestions to pilots and parametric design, and geometry manipulation tools.

                                        The software language usually used in aviation software is
                                        C++ . “Which is one of the most powerful, fast, programming languages that are used for developing flight software. Besides, like C, ISRO and NASA deploy C++ for various ground operations.”
                                        </p>
